folder: Ashland Place & Fulton Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Ashland Place, east side, between Fulton Street and Lafayette Ave.

July 5, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Ashland Place & Fulton Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Ashland Place, north from and across Fulton Street, showing the B.M.T. "El" on the latter. Note the building with the wire enclosure on the roof--it is a Y.M.C.A. branch at No. 45 Ashland Place.

May 17, 1940

folder: Fulton Street & Ashland Place, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Fulton Street, east from Ashland Place, showing the B. M. T. "El" thereon and the station at Lafayette Avenue. The parking space is on the south side of Fulton Street as seen from Ashland Place.

May 17, 1940
P. L. Sperr

2) The same, another view.
